dcterms:description: The PNC dataset contains multi-paradigm fMRI data, neurocognitive assessments, and psychiatric evaluations for 1,445 healthy adolescents ages 8-23. A subset of 620 subjects was used for predicting age, sex, and intelligence.
dcterms:title: Philadelphia Neurodevelopmental Cohort (PNC) dataset

dcterms:creator: P. Sayegh
dcterms:description: The WRAT is used to measure general intelligence through word reading subtests, and its scores were adjusted in the context of the PNC dataset.
dcterms:title: Wide Range Achievement Test (WRAT)
